1
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:18,189
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

2
00:00:18,190 --> 00:00:20,789
(Lee Kwang Soo)

3
00:00:20,790 --> 00:00:22,889
(Kim Woo Bin)

4
00:00:22,890 --> 00:00:25,129
(Doh Kyung Soo)

5
00:00:25,130 --> 00:00:28,230
(This program contains indirect advertisements.)

6
00:00:29,770 --> 00:00:32,040
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

7
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:34,539
(KKPP signed a technical training agreement...)

8
00:00:34,540 --> 00:00:36,769
(to acquire livestock farming skills.)

9
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:37,909
(Where will that be?)

10
00:00:37,910 --> 00:00:40,010
(A dairy farm)

11
00:00:40,580 --> 00:00:43,480
(KKPP technical training at a dairy farm on Jeju Island)

12
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:47,649
(The trainees visit a family-run dairy farm.)

13
00:00:47,650 --> 00:00:48,650
It's cow manure.

14
00:00:48,651 --> 00:00:49,689
(Their first assignment)

15
00:00:49,690 --> 00:00:50,690
- Is this all manure?
- Yes.

16
00:00:50,691 --> 00:00:52,290
(Cleaning cow manure)

17
00:00:52,790 --> 00:00:55,259
(They shovel cow manure endlessly.)

18
00:00:55,260 --> 00:00:57,190
(Laughing)

19
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,100
(I've never smelled this in my life.)

20
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:02,269
(While enduring the smell, they finish cleaning.)

21
00:01:02,270 --> 00:01:03,530
(Spotless)

22
00:01:04,130 --> 00:01:08,010
(The cows return to their clean home, and their training ends.)

23
00:01:08,140 --> 00:01:09,970
(However)

24
00:01:11,210 --> 00:01:14,750
(The headquarters dispatched an intern to help the tired trainees.)

25
00:01:15,410 --> 00:01:18,549
(Even the KKPP didn't know the intern's surprising appearance.)

26
00:01:18,550 --> 00:01:19,680
(What?)

27
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:24,020
(What will happen to them?)

28
00:01:24,090 --> 00:01:27,289
(Current time: 6am, the morning of their 2nd day)

29
00:01:27,290 --> 00:01:29,490
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

30
00:01:29,660 --> 00:01:30,689
Good morning.

31
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:32,030
- Good morning.
- Hello.

32
00:01:32,130 --> 00:01:34,629
- Did you enjoy dinner last night?
- Yes.

33
00:01:34,630 --> 00:01:36,199
What did you make?

34
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,800
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

35
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:39,599
- What did you make last night?
- What?

36
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,799
- Here?
- What did you cook?

37
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,640
What did I cook? It's a secret.

38
00:01:42,740 --> 00:01:44,240
Why is it a secret?

39
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:46,140
I'm so curious because it's a secret.

40
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:50,409
I'm glad that it's not raining.

41
00:01:50,410 --> 00:01:51,650
- I agree.
- Yes.

42
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:53,580
I hear that it'll be sunny today.

43
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:55,049
- Really?
- Yes.

44
00:01:55,050 --> 00:01:56,050
I'm glad to hear that.

45
00:01:57,250 --> 00:01:59,390
- It must be time for them to eat.
- Yes.

46
00:02:00,990 --> 00:02:02,929
(They're on edge before breakfast.)

47
00:02:02,930 --> 00:02:03,990
It must be breakfast time.

48
00:02:05,130 --> 00:02:06,130
(Morning Task Schedule)

49
00:02:06,131 --> 00:02:08,499
(Cleaning the feed troughs)

50
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:11,200
- They have to eat breakfast now.
- Okay.

51
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,899
These are their feed troughs.

52
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,440
You will wash them.

53
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:17,540
Push everything all the way there.

54
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,510
- They'll be eating a lot today.
- Yes.

55
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,880
The two of us will do it.

56
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,510
With a broom...

57
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:26,150
- Who wants to use this?
- I will.

58
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:28,590
Besides, I'm the CEO.

59
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,320
This is the best.

60
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:33,819
(The morning task starts.)

61
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:38,199
(When Woo Bin and Kyung Soo push the hay aside with shovels,)

62
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:42,529
(Kwang Soo finishes up with the air blower.)

63
00:02:42,530 --> 00:02:44,300
Their feed trough is really nice.

64
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:48,210
Wait just a moment.

65
00:02:50,370 --> 00:02:51,410
Hey.

66
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:53,310
Did you sleep well?

67
00:02:54,180 --> 00:02:57,410
(Saying hello to the dairy cows through the fence)

68
00:02:58,450 --> 00:03:03,350
(The KKPP trainees kick off the morning energetically.)

69
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:09,060
Goodness.

70
00:03:09,061 --> 00:03:13,099
(Cleaning quickly for the hungry cows)

71
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:16,069
Isn't it funny how they're standing back?

72
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:17,740
- Yes.
- They know what's going on.

73
00:03:18,140 --> 00:03:21,570
(Watching Kwang Soo)

74
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:28,079
(Stop filming me.)

75
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,550
It's slippery here.

76
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:33,219
However, none of us slipped.

77
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:35,820
Honestly, I couldn't help but slip.

78
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:38,319
- What?
- I couldn't help but slip.

79
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,820
It's just that your legs are weak.

80
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,859
(Payback time)

81
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:48,830
(They get back to cleaning.)

82
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:57,269
(Kyung Soo gets his revenge on the air blower.)

83
00:03:57,270 --> 00:03:58,780
How am I supposed to take this?

84
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,840
Kwang Soo.

85
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:03,780
That's exactly how I felt yesterday when he threw manure at me.

86
00:04:05,050 --> 00:04:07,150
Sir, don't these cows go out to pasture?

87
00:04:07,350 --> 00:04:09,249
Since we milk them,

88
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:12,060
keeping them out on pasture for long periods can...

89
00:04:12,290 --> 00:04:13,789
expose them to ticks...

90
00:04:13,790 --> 00:04:16,830
- So it's not good.
- and other parasites.

91
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:19,860
Treating them requires pesticides.

92
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:21,799
We can't use them...

93
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,799
- Using pesticides...
- on lactating cows.

94
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:26,600
So these cows stay indoors.

95
00:04:27,970 --> 00:04:29,170
That's fascinating.

96
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:32,880
This is all done.

97
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:35,309
You can go in and make the feed.

98
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,310
Okay.

99
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,849
(Making the feed)

100
00:04:38,850 --> 00:04:41,219
- Now...
- Do you feed them with the machine?

101
00:04:41,220 --> 00:04:43,490
Yes, let me tell you about the machine.

102
00:04:43,590 --> 00:04:45,420
These are weights in kilograms.

103
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:48,090
- My gosh.
- Distillers grains, soybean meal.

104
00:04:48,530 --> 00:04:49,930
- Alfalfa?
- Yes.

105
00:04:50,530 --> 00:04:52,400
They don't just feed them grass.

106
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:53,830
Be careful.

107
00:04:53,831 --> 00:04:56,800
- It smells really fermented.
- Right.

108
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,700
They use machines for just about everything.

109
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:02,110
(Exclaiming in awe)

110
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:05,010
(Smiling)

111
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,109
Take it off.

112
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:08,950
(The first ingredient is fermented hay.)

113
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:11,280
- There's a net.
- We have to take it off.

114
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:14,820
This is how it's piled up.

115
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:19,290
(Everything fascinates the dairy farm beginners.)

116
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:20,759
- I think that's all there is.
- Doesn't it keep coming off?

117
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:21,760
Yes.

118
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,529
(Once the trainees take off the net)

119
00:05:24,530 --> 00:05:26,200
- It's done.
- Okay.

120
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,430
- Let's go.
- Okay.

121
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:31,800
(Their senior is in charge of the finish.)

122
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,969
(Exclaiming)

123
00:05:35,970 --> 00:05:38,780
(Placing it perfectly on top of the mixer)

124
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:41,410
(Exclaiming)

125
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:44,150
(That was some perfect driving.)

126
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:46,779
(Thank you.)

127
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:47,849
This?

128
00:05:47,850 --> 00:05:50,020
Yes, 120kg of this.

129
00:05:50,790 --> 00:05:52,260
- Gosh.
- What's this?

130
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,419
- What is it?
- Isn't it puffed rice?

131
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:55,489
It's cottonseed.

132
00:05:55,490 --> 00:05:57,390
It's what's left when the cotton is removed.

133
00:05:57,490 --> 00:05:58,930
- It feels like...
- Isn't this...

134
00:06:00,530 --> 00:06:01,870
usually inside a pillow?

135
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,270
It looks like dust.

136
00:06:06,270 --> 00:06:08,569
- In pillows...
- When you crack it open,

137
00:06:08,570 --> 00:06:09,609
you'll find a seed inside.

138
00:06:09,610 --> 00:06:10,869
- Fibers?
- The seed.

139
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:11,910
- The seed?
- The seed?

140
00:06:12,010 --> 00:06:13,340
It's delicious.

141
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:15,809
- It's delicious?
- Cows like it.

142
00:06:15,810 --> 00:06:17,150
- Cows like it?
- Not for us?

143
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:19,619
- We can eat it too.
- Can we...

144
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:21,019
(Putting right in)

145
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:23,190
(Senoir Kkalloo boldly takes a bite.)

146
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:25,660
- He says that it's good.
- I don't want any.

147
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,189
Aren't you curious?

148
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:28,459
(Kyung Soo can't hold back his curiosity.)

149
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:30,690
When you crack it open, there's something inside.

150
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:32,630
There's something inside.

151
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:36,630
(There's a small seed inside the skin.)

152
00:06:36,970 --> 00:06:38,740
(Flinching)

153
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:41,910
Tell us exactly how it tastes.

154
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:43,170
I won't do it.

155
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:46,639
You just have to win. You won't be it anyway.

156
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:47,909
You won't be it anyway.

157
00:06:47,910 --> 00:06:49,950
- I have a bad feeling about it.
- I promise that it won't be you.

158
00:06:50,050 --> 00:06:51,050
I guarantee it.

159
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:52,580
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

160
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,080
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

161
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:57,990
(It's me anyway.)

162
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,630
It tastes like a sunflower seed.

163
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:03,260
It tastes like seeds?

164
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,629
Since it's a seed.

165
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:06,859
It tastes just like how it smells.

166
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,599
(Sniffing)

167
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,799
The slightly sour smell? It smells like dust.

168
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,299
It tastes just like dust.

169
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,300
One hundred and twenty...

170
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,609
In the beginning...

171
00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:18,780
Look, Kwang Soo. The shovel holds about 3kg.

172
00:07:19,010 --> 00:07:20,309
- Really?
- Yes.

173
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:21,310
(The weight is shown here.)

174
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:23,310
It's heavier than I thought.

175
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:27,080
(Endless shoveling in silence)

176
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:29,789
We got enough.

177
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:31,190
(The second ingredient complete)

178
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,319
(The third ingredient is corn meal.)

179
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,659
It smells good.

180
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:38,000
I know. I'm a little curious about the taste.

181
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:40,099
I don't exactly want to eat it,

182
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,229
- Right.
- but naturally...

183
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:43,200
- I can't help but want to eat it.
- Right.

184
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:46,599
- That's what it smells like.
- I found myself thinking...

185
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,109
that it'd be nice if it just drifted...

186
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:50,509
into my mouth.

187
00:07:50,510 --> 00:07:53,740
(Adding the fourth ingredient, soybean meal)

188
00:07:54,010 --> 00:07:55,380
The powder is flying everywhere.

189
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:01,720
It doesn't take long at all.

190
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:05,419
(The fifth ingredient is salt.)

191
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:07,119
It's made slightly salty.

192
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,560
- Sodium.
- Yes.

193
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:11,359
(Current ingredients: 1 fermented hay, 120kg of cottonseed,)

194
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,729
(120kg of distillers grains, 70kg of soybean meal, 1 bag of salt)

195
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:14,970
Have we added all?

196
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,929
No, there are still more to add.

197
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:19,040
There are more?

198
00:08:19,440 --> 00:08:22,170
We still need to add one more fermented hay.

199
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:26,080
We also need to add alfalfa and oats.

200
00:08:26,180 --> 00:08:27,980
And 270kg of feed...

201
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,009
and 120kg of corn.

202
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:31,010
(There's still a mountain of ingredients left.)

203
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:32,980
These are what we've added so far.

204
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:34,790
The CEO...

205
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:40,359
(I'll add the next hay.)

206
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:43,860
(Moving forward with a mouthful of hay)

207
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:52,700
(Spilling)

208
00:08:53,570 --> 00:08:54,570
Sir.

209
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:56,910
Sir!

210
00:08:58,180 --> 00:09:00,610
(The hay is spilling everywhere.)

211
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,980
You're going to make us work twice.

212
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:07,320
(Embarrassed)

213
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:10,689
(Making the feed isn't over yet.)

214
00:09:10,690 --> 00:09:13,620
(Another hay 1, timothy grass)

215
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,629
(Another hay 2, oats)

216
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:19,830
Isn't it too heavy?

217
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,630
(It's a full-body workout.)

218
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:30,869
(Another type of hay is going in.)

219
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:33,809
- Is this the 9th...
- It's the 9th.

220
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:34,850
The ninth?

221
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:36,550
One, two, three.

222
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:38,219
One, two, three.

223
00:09:38,220 --> 00:09:40,349
(A variety of hay is mixed to make a balanced diet for dairy cows.)

224
00:09:40,350 --> 00:09:41,420
Is it the last one?

225
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:42,820
- No, - Including that...

226
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,049
isn't that the eighth one?

227
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,220
Yes, that should be included.

228
00:09:45,860 --> 00:09:48,259
(Here comes the last hay.)

229
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:49,460
We should put these up.

230
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,269
We have two left.

231
00:09:55,270 --> 00:09:57,030
The base and...

232
00:09:57,970 --> 00:10:00,670
This comes out when you press the button.

233
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:05,410
Until 120kg of it comes out...

234
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:07,579
It'll take some time, so you can take a rest.

235
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:08,580
(Making the feed took 1 hour and 30 minutes.)

236
00:10:08,581 --> 00:10:10,049
It takes some time until it's 120kg.

237
00:10:10,050 --> 00:10:12,479
(How was it making the feed?)

238
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,150
We're inexperienced,

239
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,650
so it took us an extra hour.

240
00:10:17,590 --> 00:10:19,389
It was fun because it was my first time doing it.

241
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:20,390
- Was it fun?
- Yes.

242
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:24,130
I didn't know...

243
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:28,269
that cows needed different types of feed.

244
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:29,530
I just thought...

245
00:10:30,170 --> 00:10:33,770
that they only ate the hay we put in at first.

246
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:38,540
I had no idea that their diet was so complex.

247
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:43,780
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

248
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,419
(Lee Kwang Soo)

249
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:48,719
(Kim Woo Bin)

250
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:50,750
(Doh Kyung Soo)

251
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:57,730
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

252
00:10:58,130 --> 00:10:59,859
The feed is ready,

253
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:01,360
but you must check this.

254
00:11:01,930 --> 00:11:03,100
- If there is anyone...
- Yes.

255
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:05,040
Come out!

256
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:07,569
Come out right now.

257
00:11:07,570 --> 00:11:08,570
(The trainee is sensitive about safety.)

258
00:11:08,571 --> 00:11:09,909
(Completely empty)

259
00:11:09,910 --> 00:11:11,110
I don't think there is anyone.

260
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:12,210
Here we go.

261
00:11:13,010 --> 00:11:15,450
Kwang Soo, it's coming out this way.

262
00:11:16,150 --> 00:11:18,550
(Breakfast is getting distributed.)

263
00:11:18,650 --> 00:11:20,149
- Oh, my.
- They're eating immediately.

264
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:21,850
Look how the cows are waiting.

265
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:23,290
With their heads out.

266
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,359
They look cute.

267
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,520
(Fascinated)

268
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,690
It's not there.

269
