545
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:47,779
- No!
- Where are you going?

546
00:21:47,780 --> 00:21:49,479
This way.

547
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,850
No!

548
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:52,550
This way.

549
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:53,820
Not there.

550
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,850
- Here.
- This way.

551
00:21:57,550 --> 00:21:58,720
This way.

552
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:00,920
Here.

553
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:04,159
(Anyway, all the cows successfully go to school.)

554
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,289
It's excited.

555
00:22:05,290 --> 00:22:09,700
(Anyway, all the cows successfully go to school.)

556
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:13,540
It's very wide here too.

557
00:22:14,170 --> 00:22:16,440
(The range was hidden by the thick fog yesterday.)

558
00:22:17,610 --> 00:22:18,909
- It's all the way until there?
- Yes.

559
00:22:18,910 --> 00:22:19,939
It's really large.

560
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:20,940
(On a bright day, you can see how wide the field is.)

561
00:22:20,941 --> 00:22:22,010
The weather is really nice.

562
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:23,910
It's so wide.

563
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:27,279
Right, this is Jeju Island.

564
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:28,619
(The cows roam around the green field.)

565
00:22:28,620 --> 00:22:29,950
I totally forgot.

566
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:32,020
I totally forgot about it.

567
00:22:32,990 --> 00:22:35,489
The cow's hoof looks cute.

568
00:22:35,490 --> 00:22:36,690
(A peaceful scene)

569
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:38,389
It's a photo zone?

570
00:22:38,390 --> 00:22:40,300
(A photo zone made by the CEO)

571
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:42,200
Sit down. I'll take a picture of you.

572
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:43,900
Sit over there.

573
00:22:45,370 --> 00:22:47,940
Looking good.

574
00:22:49,010 --> 00:22:50,570
What are you doing, sir?

575
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,710
Are you Kyung Soo's fan?

576
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:54,080
(He can't hear him.)

577
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,809
Sir, can you hear me?

578
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:57,049
(Together this time)

579
00:22:57,050 --> 00:22:58,280
- Sir.
- Yes?

580
00:22:58,580 --> 00:22:59,619
I'm busy now.

581
00:22:59,620 --> 00:23:00,620
(Laughing)

582
00:23:00,620 --> 00:23:01,620
What...

583
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:03,389
- One, two, three.
- You should look after the cows.

584
00:23:03,390 --> 00:23:04,619
(The CEO only has Kyung Soo on his mind.)

585
00:23:04,620 --> 00:23:06,190
They're all at the corner.

586
00:23:06,490 --> 00:23:07,819
I'll herd them here.

587
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:08,820
(The cows are crowded at the grass-less corner.)

588
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:09,960
Let's go.

589
00:23:09,961 --> 00:23:11,159
(Kwang Soo leads them to the area with a lot of grass...)

590
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:12,160
(on his own.)

591
00:23:12,161 --> 00:23:13,860
Let's go.

592
00:23:14,660 --> 00:23:15,900
(Hollering)

593
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:18,969
(The cows run toward the area with delicious grass.)

594
00:23:18,970 --> 00:23:19,970
Let's go.

595
00:23:19,971 --> 00:23:21,200
(The cows run toward the area with delicious grass.)

596
00:23:21,870 --> 00:23:26,009
(Cow: Passing by.)

597
00:23:26,010 --> 00:23:28,380
They're going back home.

598
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:30,809
It's open.

599
00:23:30,810 --> 00:23:31,910
What's open?

600
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:33,680
No!

601
00:23:35,520 --> 00:23:36,520
Close it!

602
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:39,960
(A big accident is prevented thanks to Woo Bin's quick catch.)

603
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:42,119
(What a pity.)

604
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:43,130
Let's go.

605
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,699
- If I herd them that way...
- Yes.

606
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,030
Is there a way there?

607
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:48,830
- There is, over here.
- Okay.

608
00:23:49,570 --> 00:23:51,130
Hey.

609
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:53,639
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

610
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,799
Let's go.

611
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,240
(Kwangder Collie and Woopherd start to work in tandem.)

612
00:23:57,810 --> 00:23:59,380
The cows look the cutest when they eat.

613
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:04,480
(Finally arrived at the spot with tasty grass)

614
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:07,550
(Spaced out)

615
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:08,850
What time is it?

616
00:24:09,550 --> 00:24:11,350
(Current time: 10am)

617
00:24:11,990 --> 00:24:13,190
Only that?

618
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:14,920
(They got to work at 6am today.)

619
00:24:14,921 --> 00:24:16,230
We started way too early.

620
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:18,290
I thought it'd be 12pm or 1pm.

621
00:24:20,630 --> 00:24:21,700
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

622
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,229
Can I rest for a bit? Just three minutes.

623
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:25,800
Running tired me out too.

624
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,310
My voice became hoarse.

625
00:24:30,810 --> 00:24:33,009
But aren't I good at making this sound?

626
00:24:33,010 --> 00:24:34,010
Yes, you are.

627
00:24:34,110 --> 00:24:35,610
(Encore)

628
00:24:36,180 --> 00:24:38,850
I noticed you copied me a few times.

629
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:40,520
I learned from you.

630
00:24:40,650 --> 00:24:42,419
It wasn't the other way round?

631
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:43,849
- I thought so too.
- I copied him.

632
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:45,350
He copied me.

633
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,860
It felt unpleasant and nice at the same time.

634
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:50,330
(He turns out to be the inventor of the holler.)

635
00:24:50,690 --> 00:24:54,060
I also noticed Lal copying me a few times.

636
00:24:54,230 --> 00:24:56,029
- Please make it clear to him.
- Okay.

637
00:24:56,030 --> 00:24:57,970
(How was the morning training?)

638
00:24:58,530 --> 00:25:00,840
I'm starting to get attached to them.

639
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:03,070
At first, they were too big,

640
00:25:04,140 --> 00:25:05,739
which scared me a bit.

641
00:25:05,740 --> 00:25:07,040
But now that I keep seeing them,

642
00:25:07,610 --> 00:25:09,780
they look cute. They have kind eyes.

643
00:25:10,850 --> 00:25:13,179
It's like watching my child having fun...

644
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,720
on a playground.

645
00:25:16,050 --> 00:25:18,650
I give them food and feel happy watching them eat.

646
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,560
Seeing the milk makes me feel proud of them.

647
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:26,629
I've already become someone...

648
00:25:26,630 --> 00:25:28,299
who was born and raised here.

649
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:29,930
(Here he goes again.)

650
00:25:30,470 --> 00:25:32,000
What I'm most curious about is...

651
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:35,770
what Mr. Kkalloo and Mr. Lal...

652
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:37,740
will eat.

653
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:41,540
I'll steal what they eat.

654
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:42,910
I want to eat together.

655
00:25:43,380 --> 00:25:45,479
(The question was about the morning training.)

656
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:46,650
We should go together.

657
00:25:48,780 --> 00:25:50,550
Would you like to have breakfast with us?

658
00:25:51,850 --> 00:25:52,860
Lamb?

659
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:55,019
- Do you like lamb?
- Yes.

660
00:25:55,020 --> 00:25:57,460
Lamb is my favorite.

661
00:25:57,630 --> 00:25:59,060
- Your favorite.
- Let's have lamb.

662
00:25:59,530 --> 00:26:01,960
- Let's eat together.
- My company will treat you...

663
00:26:02,870 --> 00:26:03,930
to lamb today.

664
00:26:04,170 --> 00:26:05,370
Sounds good.

665
00:26:05,530 --> 00:26:07,099
(Smiling widely)

666
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:09,770
- So you like free stuff.
- Yes.

667
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:11,570
- Of course.
- It's our treat.

668
00:26:12,610 --> 00:26:13,980
It won't be open yet.

669
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:15,540
- It must not be open yet.
- It's not open yet?

670
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,079
It opens in the evening.

671
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:18,479
(The lamb restaurant is closed in the morning.)

672
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:19,820
In Nepal,

673
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:23,219
we eat goat and lamb...

674
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:25,349
- Really?
- the most.

675
00:26:25,350 --> 00:26:26,619
- And chicken.
- In Nepal.

676
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:27,789
(Mr. Kkalloo recommends goat meat.)

677
00:26:27,790 --> 00:26:29,190
Let's go have goat meat.

678
00:26:29,230 --> 00:26:30,960
- Okay.
- Let's go.

679
00:26:31,990 --> 00:26:33,060
What about Mr. Lal?

680
00:26:33,430 --> 00:26:35,030
Lal likes to sleep.

681
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,400
- Sleep?
- He'd rather sleep.

682
00:26:37,570 --> 00:26:38,769
He's holed up somewhere...

683
00:26:38,770 --> 00:26:40,039
and sleeping?

684
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:41,200
I'm not sure about that.

685
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:43,310
- What... Mr. Lal!
- He...

686
00:26:43,540 --> 00:26:44,970
He sleeps whenever he has the chance.

687
00:26:45,340 --> 00:26:46,480
Mr. Lal!

688
00:26:46,910 --> 00:26:48,009
Around 8pm...

689
00:26:48,010 --> 00:26:49,310
Everyone is working.

690
00:26:49,410 --> 00:26:51,510
You clearly look like you just woke up!

691
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:55,280
You clearly look like you just woke up.

692
00:26:56,790 --> 00:26:58,920
How can you sleep when everyone else is working?

693
00:27:00,290 --> 00:27:02,660
What happened to your hair suddenly?

694
00:27:04,590 --> 00:27:06,929
We're going to eat goat meat.

695
00:27:06,930 --> 00:27:08,160
- Goat?
- Yes.

696
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:10,130
- Join us.
- Okay.

697
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,370
Go wash your face. You need to wake up.

698
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:15,699
Let's go to eat goat now.

699
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:16,810
Okay.

700
00:27:17,140 --> 00:27:18,409
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

701
00:27:18,410 --> 00:27:20,110
- We'll take our stuff.
- Just take our stuff.

702
00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:24,009
(They stop by the hut to get their stuff.)

703
00:27:24,010 --> 00:27:25,649
- Yes. Is this milk?
- This...

704
00:27:25,650 --> 00:27:26,980
- Yes.
- Goodness.

705
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:29,019
It's a bit hot now.

706
00:27:29,020 --> 00:27:30,149
It's hot?

707
00:27:30,150 --> 00:27:31,819
Did you boil it?

708
00:27:31,820 --> 00:27:33,790
Yes, I double-boiled it.

709
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:35,289
(They've really wanted to try it.)

710
00:27:35,290 --> 00:27:36,629
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

711
00:27:36,630 --> 00:27:37,830
Thank you.

712
00:27:38,130 --> 00:27:39,159
(Sniffing)

713
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:40,160
(Surprised)

714
00:27:40,161 --> 00:27:42,770
- Is it savory?
- It smells like condensed milk.

715
00:27:44,070 --> 00:27:45,499
(Amazed)

716
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:46,640
Why?

717
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:49,310
How should I explain this?

718
00:27:49,740 --> 00:27:51,840
It's tragic that I can't transmit the smell.

719
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,580
Smell this.

720
00:27:55,010 --> 00:27:56,209
Gosh, what is this?

721
00:27:56,210 --> 00:27:57,549
- This...
- It's so thick.

722
00:27:57,550 --> 00:27:59,249
- I...
- Is it good?

723
00:27:59,250 --> 00:28:00,980
This reminds me of when I was an infant.

724
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:06,790
(Woo Bin drinks it first.)

725
00:28:08,260 --> 00:28:10,130
- Gosh, it's so good.
- It's so thick.

726
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,160
- Is it good?
- It's so good.

727
00:28:13,130 --> 00:28:14,159
This...

728
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:15,399
(Kyung Soo drinks it too.)

729
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:16,930
How should I describe this?

730
00:28:17,470 --> 00:28:18,969
- The vending machine...
- Kwang Soo.

731
00:28:18,970 --> 00:28:20,140
- Quick, drink it.
- Drink it.

732
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:22,040
(Impressed)

733
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:26,280
(Kwang Soo tastes the fresh milk.)

734
00:28:26,810 --> 00:28:29,510
No sugar is added, yet it's sweet.

735
00:28:30,010 --> 00:28:31,379
What I drank until today wasn't milk.

736
00:28:31,380 --> 00:28:32,550
How is this possible?

737
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,550
It's so thick and nice.

738
00:28:36,390 --> 00:28:37,719
- It's sweet.
- Try it.

739
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:40,119
Directors, try it before it cools down.

740
00:28:40,120 --> 00:28:42,120
Gogo and Farmfarm drink this.

741
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,560
No wonder...

742
00:28:43,590 --> 00:28:44,960
they had the mad eyes.

743
00:28:47,630 --> 00:28:49,770
- I want to have this with bread.
- Me too.

744
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:52,100
If you dip it in milk...

745
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:53,369
(Nyom)

746
00:28:53,370 --> 00:28:54,399
- It's so tasty.
- Shall we leave some here...

747
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,440
and buy bread on our way back?

748
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,640
Sounds good.

749
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:00,010
It'd taste amazing if you made a latte out of this.

750
00:29:00,410 --> 00:29:02,610
We shouldn't overlook this.

751
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:04,480
Sir.

752
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:08,180
We should sign a contract about this.

753
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:11,350
- If you make a latte out of it, - Latte?

754
00:29:11,790 --> 00:29:13,059
it'll be amazing.

755
00:29:13,060 --> 00:29:14,960
(Business ideas spring up from the fresh milk.)

756
00:29:15,990 --> 00:29:17,929
(They'll wash the boots before they go for breakfast.)

757
00:29:17,930 --> 00:29:19,400
No, this...

758
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,260
Thank you.

759
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,229
(Kwang Soo washes Mr. Kkalloo's boots.)

760
00:29:24,230 --> 00:29:25,899
- I'll wash yours.
- It's okay.

761
00:29:25,900 --> 00:29:27,370
- No.
- My gosh.

762
00:29:27,540 --> 00:29:28,740
Thank you.

763
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:31,040
(They bond over washing each other's boots.)

764
00:29:31,410 --> 00:29:32,470
Sir.

765
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:34,579
I'm sorry, but can I link arms with you?

766
00:29:34,580 --> 00:29:36,080
What? Okay.

767
00:29:37,210 --> 00:29:40,980
(Kkalloo and trainees head to the restaurant together.)

768
00:29:41,980 --> 00:29:43,619
(Crash)

769
00:29:43,620 --> 00:29:44,789
Gosh, it fell.

770
00:29:44,790 --> 00:29:45,850
It fell.

771
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:50,790
(A cow collapsed onto the floor.)

772
00:29:51,330 --> 00:29:53,400
(As it was walking out after a meal,)

773
00:29:55,530 --> 00:29:57,630
(it tripped on another cow.)

774
00:29:58,600 --> 00:30:01,340
(It tries to stand on its own.)

775
00:30:04,170 --> 00:30:07,010
(It isn't easy to do so due to its weight, about 700kg.)

776
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:11,450
(Mr. Kkalloo hurriedly runs to it.)

777
00:30:11,950 --> 00:30:15,280
(Mr. Lal came with a rescue tool.)

778
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:18,790
- That's the pelvis support?
- Yes.

779
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:25,630
(The clasp is tightly fixed around its pelvis.)

780
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:29,059
(He goes in to check on the cow.)

781
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:30,100
Let's go.

782
00:30:31,630 --> 00:30:33,840
That's what happened to its legs. It must be painful.

783
00:30:33,970 --> 00:30:35,170
Of course it is.

784
00:30:35,340 --> 00:30:37,139
(The hind legs are split to each side.)

785
00:30:37,140 --> 00:30:40,340
It holds together the bones.

786
00:30:42,140 --> 00:30:43,380
It must hurt a lot.

787
00:30:44,510 --> 00:30:46,850
When it falls down with its legs split like that,

788
00:30:47,580 --> 00:30:49,689
it might sprain...

789
00:30:49,690 --> 00:30:51,850
its hip joint.

790
00:30:51,990 --> 00:30:53,860
Once that happens, it can't stand up on its own.

791
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:55,720
Once sprained, it's easy to sprain again.

792
00:30:56,390 --> 00:30:58,359
So we make it stand up...

793
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:02,660
and tie a support to hold it together.

794
00:31:05,430 --> 00:31:10,710
(The farm's CEO drives over a tractor.)

795
00:31:11,970 --> 00:31:15,110
(He ties it tightly to the tractor.)

796
00:31:16,580 --> 00:31:19,650
(He will lift it up so the cow can stand up.)

797
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:21,519
This.

798
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:23,250
(He drives the tractor carefully.)

799
00:31:25,690 --> 00:31:27,619
He reverses the tractor bit by bit.

800
00:31:27,620 --> 00:31:28,620
(The cow slowly stands up.)

801
00:31:28,860 --> 00:31:31,430
(It tries its best.)

802
00:31:32,230 --> 00:31:34,600
(Synced to its pain)

803
00:31:34,930 --> 00:31:37,530
(They moved to a spacious place so it's easier to lift it up.)

804
00:31:38,500 --> 00:31:39,500
It must be painful.

805
00:31:41,170 --> 00:31:42,970
Lal, the band.

806
00:31:45,970 --> 00:31:50,880
(The band to fix the leg is here.)

807
00:31:51,510 --> 00:31:52,780
I see.

808
00:31:52,980 --> 00:31:55,450
They must use the band to tie around the legs.

809
00:31:56,150 --> 00:31:58,150
- Both legs.
- Tie the legs together?

810
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:00,859
(The hind legs need to be tied with a band.)

811
00:32:00,860 --> 00:32:02,220
Because the legs are spread apart.

812
00:32:05,460 --> 00:32:08,800
(With a bit of tractor's help, the cow stands up soon.)

813
00:32:12,230 --> 00:32:14,669
(The seniors try to tie the band.)

814
00:32:14,670 --> 00:32:16,770
(But the cow doesn't budge.)

815
00:32:17,810 --> 00:32:21,680
(Kwang Soo, who was watching quietly,)

816
00:32:22,580 --> 00:32:26,480
(helps out the seniors.)

817
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:28,380
Do I pull harder?

818
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:32,019
This needs to be tied around here.

819
00:32:32,020 --> 00:32:33,819
- I see.
- Here.

820
00:32:33,820 --> 00:32:34,860
Pull how?

821
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:36,759
One, two, three.

822
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:38,160
(Woo Bin joins too.)

823
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:40,430
- One, two, three.
- Three.

824
00:32:41,630 --> 00:32:43,069
(They pull as hard as they can.)

825
00:32:43,070 --> 00:32:44,130
It worked.

826
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:45,999
Did it work? Do we need to pull harder?

827
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:47,140
It didn't work.

828
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:49,099
It's not in the right place.

829
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:50,110
(3 people aren't enough.)

830
00:32:51,370 --> 00:32:52,639
- Goodness.
- Wait.

831
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:54,210
(It's hard to tie the band because the legs keep spreading.)

832
00:32:54,410 --> 00:32:55,480
One, two, three.

833
00:32:55,940 --> 00:32:57,110
- One, two, three.
- Three.

834
00:32:58,350 --> 00:32:59,379
One, two, three.

835
00:32:59,380 --> 00:33:01,250
(They keep trying.)

836
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:02,680
It fell.

837
00:33:03,420 --> 00:33:04,520
It fell forward.

838
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:08,690
(What should we do?)

839
00:33:10,690 --> 00:33:15,200
(At that moment, Mr. Lal comes back with a rope.)

840
00:33:16,730 --> 00:33:20,270
(The CEO ties the rope around one leg of the cow.)

841
00:33:21,100 --> 00:33:22,739
One, two, pull.

842
00:33:22,740 --> 00:33:24,110
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

843
00:33:24,210 --> 00:33:26,380
It worked.

844
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:32,380
(They quickly tie the band around the hind legs.)

845
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,519
- Done.
- Is it done?

846
00:33:33,520 --> 00:33:34,620
- Let go.
- Yes.

847
00:33:34,950 --> 00:33:36,020
Pull it.

848
00:33:37,820 --> 00:33:41,620
(Thankfully, they managed to tie the band properly.)

849
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:43,690
It must've been painful.

850
00:33:45,530 --> 00:33:49,360
(Feeling pity and concern)

851
00:33:49,830 --> 00:33:51,900
Will it get treated now?

852
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:53,940
It has had bad legs since before.

853
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:55,170
Since before?

854
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:56,609
It has bad legs.

855
00:33:56,610 --> 00:33:58,169
The ground is slippery.

856
00:33:58,170 --> 00:33:59,580
When it came to eat,

857
00:33:59,910 --> 00:34:03,250
