876
00:34:36,810 --> 00:34:37,880
- Please go in.
- Go in.

877
00:34:38,210 --> 00:34:39,949
- Sir.
- Oh, yes.

878
00:34:39,950 --> 00:34:41,020
(They came to have lunch.)

879
00:34:41,250 --> 00:34:42,449
It smells good.

880
00:34:42,450 --> 00:34:44,220
- Let's go in.
- Do you come here often?

881
00:34:44,420 --> 00:34:45,490
Yes, occasionally.

882
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:51,090
Let me do it, sir.

883
00:34:51,190 --> 00:34:52,260
Please sit down.

884
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:55,500
(Everyone takes a seat.)

885
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,269
One boiled goat and one spicy stir-fried goat.

886
00:34:57,270 --> 00:34:58,369
- Half on each table. Yes.
- Okay.

887
00:34:58,370 --> 00:35:00,200
- I'll prepare it.
- Thank you.

888
00:35:01,140 --> 00:35:02,340
I've never tried it before.

889
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:04,139
You'll definitely like it.

890
00:35:04,140 --> 00:35:05,340
- Really?
- I have a feeling.

891
00:35:06,540 --> 00:35:07,610
What kind of feeling?

892
00:35:07,710 --> 00:35:09,009
Just a feeling, you know.

893
00:35:09,010 --> 00:35:10,910
- I have a feeling.
- That kind of feeling.

894
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:14,420
Guess I should show off my granddaughter.

895
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:17,550
- How old is she?
- Six.

896
00:35:17,650 --> 00:35:19,550
- I see.
- She must be so cute.

897
00:35:22,660 --> 00:35:24,360
- She's cute.
- She's so cute.

898
00:35:25,230 --> 00:35:26,959
- She's so cute.
- How cute.

899
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:28,060
She looks like her dad.

900
00:35:29,430 --> 00:35:31,230
- She looks playful.
- Yes.

901
00:35:31,930 --> 00:35:33,099
Do you have a child, Kkalloo?

902
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:34,370
They're dads too.

903
00:35:34,470 --> 00:35:35,840
- Really?
- Really?

904
00:35:36,570 --> 00:35:38,609
Lal has a son, and Kkalloo has a daughter.

905
00:35:38,610 --> 00:35:40,879
(Looking for his daughter's photos)

906
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,009
This is her.

907
00:35:42,010 --> 00:35:43,450
So cute.

908
00:35:45,150 --> 00:35:46,550
- So cute.
- When was this?

909
00:35:46,850 --> 00:35:48,979
- Is this now?
- Yes, it's now.

910
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:51,050
- Now?
- She's a baby.

911
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:52,819
How old is she?

912
00:35:52,820 --> 00:35:55,019
- Only a few months old, right?
- About four months old.

913
00:35:55,020 --> 00:35:56,060
Four months old?

914
00:35:56,660 --> 00:35:58,730
- You must miss her so much.
- Yes.

915
00:35:59,230 --> 00:36:00,830
He hasn't met his daughter yet.

916
00:36:00,930 --> 00:36:01,959
- You haven't?
- No.

917
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:02,960
He hasn't physically met her yet.

918
00:36:02,961 --> 00:36:04,069
After your wife got pregnant,

919
00:36:04,070 --> 00:36:05,730
you had to come back to Korea right away?

920
00:36:06,130 --> 00:36:07,639
You must miss your family a lot.

921
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:08,640
Yes.

922
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:12,040
Kkalloo has a house in Nepal. Was it 2-story or 3-story?

923
00:36:12,140 --> 00:36:13,209
Three-story.

924
00:36:13,210 --> 00:36:15,380
- You live in a three-story house?
- You're rich, sir.

925
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,810
With the money he earned here.

926
00:36:17,250 --> 00:36:19,110
Hold on. You live in a three-story house?

927
00:36:20,980 --> 00:36:22,680
- I built it.
- He built it himself.

928
00:36:23,820 --> 00:36:27,259
I bought the land with the money I earned here.

929
00:36:27,260 --> 00:36:28,690
- You're rich.
- So cool.

930
00:36:29,490 --> 00:36:31,760
Mr. Lal, when did you get married?

931
00:36:32,590 --> 00:36:33,699
When I was 20.

932
00:36:33,700 --> 00:36:35,229
- Twenty?
- You got married very early.

933
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:36,300
You were so young.

934
00:36:36,570 --> 00:36:39,170
I got married last year.

935
00:36:39,670 --> 00:36:42,000
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

936
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:45,670
I was the MC of the wedding.

937
00:36:47,310 --> 00:36:48,980
Should we clap for him?

938
00:36:49,410 --> 00:36:50,410
To congratulate him.

939
00:36:51,010 --> 00:36:52,909
Congratulations.

940
00:36:52,910 --> 00:36:54,920
(Getting applauded for the marriage that happened half a year ago)

941
00:36:56,380 --> 00:36:57,490
Thank you.

942
00:36:59,420 --> 00:37:01,490
Do you two live together now?

943
00:37:01,590 --> 00:37:02,590
Yes.

944
00:37:03,060 --> 00:37:04,460
You must be very close.

945
00:37:04,860 --> 00:37:07,130
Kkalloo is older, so he takes great care of Lal.

946
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:10,000
- I can see that.
- Yes.

947
00:37:10,100 --> 00:37:11,870
How does Mr. Kkalloo treat you well?

948
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:14,799
(Translating for Lal, who isn't very fluent in Korean)

949
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,810
Mr. Kkalloo's face became red as he talked about this.

950
00:37:17,340 --> 00:37:18,440
He became very red.

951
00:37:19,010 --> 00:37:21,240
My face is naturally red.

952
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:23,950
It was pale just now.

953
00:37:25,310 --> 00:37:26,950
What did Mr. Lal say?

954
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:30,450
(Mr. Lal replies in Nepali.)

955
00:37:30,720 --> 00:37:32,189
When he first came here,

956
00:37:32,190 --> 00:37:35,590
I cooked for him,

957
00:37:35,690 --> 00:37:37,360
and work-wise...

958
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:39,800
- You taught him well.
- I taught him well.

959
00:37:40,130 --> 00:37:42,499
When he does his job poorly,

960
00:37:42,500 --> 00:37:44,169
I don't scold him.

961
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:46,940
- Yes, you don't get annoyed.
- I don't get annoyed.

962
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:50,210
- He's such a good colleague.
- What he said wasn't that long.

963
00:37:51,710 --> 00:37:54,139
Mr. Lal's sentence was short,

964
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:55,239
but your translation is so long.

965
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:57,249
He spoke shortly,

966
00:37:57,250 --> 00:38:00,250
but that's what he meant.

967
00:38:00,550 --> 00:38:02,649
(While they get to know each other better...)

968
00:38:02,650 --> 00:38:03,789
- Here.
- Enjoy your food.

969
00:38:03,790 --> 00:38:04,790
Enjoy your food.

970
00:38:06,490 --> 00:38:07,589
It looks good.

971
00:38:07,590 --> 00:38:09,789
- It's too far.
- Eat up.

972
00:38:09,790 --> 00:38:11,290
- Okay.
- Go ahead.

973
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:12,560
Thank you for the food.

974
00:38:12,561 --> 00:38:14,260
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

975
00:38:16,970 --> 00:38:19,130
(As they skipped breakfast and worked since early morning,)

976
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:23,810
(everyone enjoys the food.)

977
00:38:24,910 --> 00:38:27,910
(At that time, in the farm)

978
00:38:30,080 --> 00:38:34,720
(A relaxing afternoon just like any other day)

979
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:42,289
(Or so they thought.)

980
00:38:42,290 --> 00:38:43,430
(Slam)

981
00:38:48,100 --> 00:38:52,099
(The ranch's gate has opened.)

982
00:38:52,100 --> 00:38:56,670
(A relaxing afternoon just like any other day)

983
00:39:02,010 --> 00:39:04,249
(Or so they thought.)

984
00:39:04,250 --> 00:39:05,310
(Slam)

985
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:13,360
(The ranch's gate has opened.)

986
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:16,760
(Sneaking out)

987
00:39:17,830 --> 00:39:21,600
(The cows leave the ranch.)

988
00:39:22,930 --> 00:39:24,129
(Let's escape!)

989
00:39:24,130 --> 00:39:26,129
(Let's go out! Let's go!)

990
00:39:26,130 --> 00:39:27,740
(Quick, let's go!)

991
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:32,070
(Escaping as a herd)

992
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:37,250
(The crew is filming nearby, unaware of the situation.)

993
00:39:38,210 --> 00:39:39,510
- Goodness.
- What is it?

994
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:42,220
- The cows escaped.
- What?

995
00:39:42,650 --> 00:39:43,690
How did they open the gate?

996
00:39:46,090 --> 00:39:47,090
Oh, no.

997
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:48,760
What?

998
00:39:50,190 --> 00:39:51,289
Is it okay not to alert the owner?

999
00:39:51,290 --> 00:39:53,159
We need to tell him. Hold on.

1000
00:39:53,160 --> 00:39:55,029
(That is that, and filming is filming.)

1001
00:39:55,030 --> 00:39:57,329
But everyone went to have lunch.

1002
00:39:57,330 --> 00:39:58,370
Exactly.

1003
00:39:58,730 --> 00:39:59,769
What should we do?

1004
00:39:59,770 --> 00:40:01,100
Should I just herd them?

1005
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,900
We should text the crew group chat.

1006
00:40:04,540 --> 00:40:07,910
(Every single one of them leaves the ranch.)

1007
00:40:08,610 --> 00:40:12,510
(Leaving behind the 99,174m² wide green field,)

1008
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:18,490
(they escape in a row.)

1009
