1040
00:41:41,570 --> 00:41:42,739
(Bumping)

1041
00:41:42,740 --> 00:41:46,510
(There's not even time to feel the pain of bumping into the iron gate.)

1042
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:50,979
(Following the direction the other production crew ran in)

1043
00:41:50,980 --> 00:41:52,150
(Surprised)

1044
00:41:53,850 --> 00:41:55,750
I think they escaped from that range.

1045
00:41:56,580 --> 00:41:57,690
What about here?

1046
00:41:58,750 --> 00:41:59,750
What do we do?

1047
00:42:00,590 --> 00:42:02,489
(The other production crew is working,)

1048
00:42:02,490 --> 00:42:04,390
(oblivious to the current situation.)

1049
00:42:04,460 --> 00:42:06,729
(Mounting a camera)

1050
00:42:06,730 --> 00:42:08,330
Why are the cows outside?

1051
00:42:08,830 --> 00:42:09,830
What?

1052
00:42:11,130 --> 00:42:12,130
What?

1053
00:42:13,130 --> 00:42:14,139
Hold on.

1054
00:42:14,140 --> 00:42:15,370
Why are the cows out here?

1055
00:42:15,970 --> 00:42:17,810
(How did this suddenly happen?)

1056
00:42:17,970 --> 00:42:20,480
The men left for lunch. What now?

1057
00:42:21,410 --> 00:42:22,810
Guys, go back inside!

1058
00:42:23,110 --> 00:42:24,110
Go inside.

1059
00:42:24,380 --> 00:42:25,380
Go inside.

1060
00:42:25,380 --> 00:42:26,380
(Beating a dead horse)

1061
00:42:26,610 --> 00:42:29,749
(Hearing the ruckus,)

1062
00:42:29,750 --> 00:42:32,050
(the bystanders gather.)

1063
00:42:32,420 --> 00:42:34,219
- Block that place, Eun Bi!
- The road is blocked.

1064
00:42:34,220 --> 00:42:35,220
(Screaming)

1065
00:42:35,221 --> 00:42:37,089
No! Stop!

1066
00:42:37,090 --> 00:42:39,860
- Stop!
- No! Go back inside!

1067
00:42:40,300 --> 00:42:43,329
(The farm staff and production crew run around chasing the cows.)

1068
00:42:43,330 --> 00:42:44,430
Where were they?

1069
00:42:44,930 --> 00:42:46,570
Where did they escape from?

1070
00:42:46,770 --> 00:42:48,170
- The range.
- I see.

1071
00:42:48,970 --> 00:42:49,970
Guys.

1072
00:42:49,970 --> 00:42:50,970
(The juvenile cows are running in all directions.)

1073
00:42:51,370 --> 00:42:52,370
No, over here.

1074
00:42:52,371 --> 00:42:54,739
- This much?
- Yes, thank you.

1075
00:42:54,740 --> 00:42:56,509
- Do you want more?
- No, it's okay.

1076
00:42:56,510 --> 00:42:57,749
- The soup is amazing.
- Right?

1077
00:42:57,750 --> 00:42:58,750
It's good.

1078
00:43:00,150 --> 00:43:01,520
Behind.

1079
00:43:03,180 --> 00:43:06,190
(The juvenile cows aren't listening at all.)

1080
00:43:06,420 --> 00:43:07,690
How do we get them back in?

1081
00:43:08,460 --> 00:43:09,460
I don't know.

1082
00:43:10,430 --> 00:43:11,490
I'm losing it.

1083
00:43:11,990 --> 00:43:12,990
Hey!

1084
00:43:13,930 --> 00:43:15,000
Come this way!

1085
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:16,760
(Impressed)

1086
00:43:17,270 --> 00:43:18,900
It has a familiar taste.

1087
00:43:19,570 --> 00:43:20,570
- Right?
- Yes.

1088
00:43:20,571 --> 00:43:21,639
- Is it okay?
- Yes, it's good.

1089
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:22,670
I'm glad.

1090
00:43:23,510 --> 00:43:24,940
Good. They're going back inside.

1091
00:43:25,170 --> 00:43:27,140
(The cows are finally listening.)

1092
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:29,310
Go back in, cows!

1093
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:31,279
- Where do we send them to?
- This way!

1094
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:32,580
- The range!
- Over there?

1095
00:43:34,620 --> 00:43:36,250
This way. Yes, move it.

1096
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:37,920
Keep moving.

1097
00:43:37,920 --> 00:43:38,920
(Back to the range)

1098
00:43:39,390 --> 00:43:40,989
The range.

1099
00:43:40,990 --> 00:43:43,629
(Ranch tip: Animals, including cows, sheep, horses, deer, and more,)

1100
00:43:43,630 --> 00:43:46,290
(feel secure together, so they move in herds.)

1101
00:43:48,130 --> 00:43:50,899
(After a brief escape from reality,)

1102
00:43:50,900 --> 00:43:51,970
Go inside.

1103
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:54,540
(the juvenile cows go back to school.)

1104
00:43:54,970 --> 00:43:56,910
- That's it.
- All set.

1105
00:44:00,580 --> 00:44:02,910
(Most return without a fight.)

1106
00:44:03,510 --> 00:44:04,510
Let's go.

1107
00:44:05,150 --> 00:44:06,809
(But some hold out.)

1108
00:44:06,810 --> 00:44:08,750
- Yes.
- Good job.

1109
00:44:09,920 --> 00:44:10,920
Well done.

1110
00:44:10,921 --> 00:44:12,690
(Some even run away until the end.)

1111
00:44:12,750 --> 00:44:14,520
Okay, this way.

1112
00:44:15,390 --> 00:44:16,460
Here we go. Please.

1113
00:44:16,660 --> 00:44:19,030
Please go inside. Please.

1114
00:44:19,330 --> 00:44:20,630
All set.

1115
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:22,000
Good job.

1116
00:44:22,530 --> 00:44:25,230
(Even the last cow is now back in school.)

1117
00:44:28,900 --> 00:44:30,409
(The range has found peace again.)

1118
00:44:30,410 --> 00:44:32,539
- To think this would happen.
- Right?

1119
00:44:32,540 --> 00:44:34,279
Does this happen quite often?

1120
00:44:34,280 --> 00:44:35,739
No, it doesn't. It never happens.

1121
00:44:35,740 --> 00:44:40,249
There are adult cows that do escape every now and then.

1122
00:44:40,250 --> 00:44:41,319
But they go back inside...

1123
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:42,820
from the yard when we tell them to.

1124
00:44:43,120 --> 00:44:45,020
The gate opening and all. That was interesting.

1125
00:44:45,290 --> 00:44:47,820
(After the fun yet uncommon event)

1126
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:50,459
Okay, got it.

1127
00:44:50,460 --> 00:44:51,460
How did it go?

1128
00:44:52,660 --> 00:44:55,029
Director, the cows are back inside.

1129
00:44:55,030 --> 00:44:56,030
- Are they?
- Yes.

1130
00:44:56,031 --> 00:44:57,070
What a relief.

1131
00:44:57,630 --> 00:44:59,269
- Was it just 1 cow?
- All except 2 cows.

1132
00:44:59,270 --> 00:45:01,200
- All of them escaped?
- Yes.

1133
00:45:01,700 --> 00:45:03,370
And they herded them back inside?

1134
00:45:04,370 --> 00:45:06,740
Unexpected incidents often happen on farms.

1135
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:09,939
Cows escaping sounds like a big problem,

1136
00:45:09,940 --> 00:45:11,810
but you were all so calm.

1137
00:45:12,450 --> 00:45:15,049
It's because I know the place.

1138
00:45:15,050 --> 00:45:16,649
I know that it's gated all around...

1139
00:45:16,650 --> 00:45:18,349
and the cows simply needed to be herded.

1140
00:45:18,350 --> 00:45:19,849
I have the whole process in my head.

1141
00:45:19,850 --> 00:45:22,820
(A situation he could handle entirely in his head)

1142
00:45:23,730 --> 00:45:25,029
Earlier, when we were having lunch...

1143
00:45:25,030 --> 00:45:26,189
(Shaking)

1144
00:45:26,190 --> 00:45:27,730
Come on.

1145
00:45:28,730 --> 00:45:29,959
That's not true.

1146
00:45:29,960 --> 00:45:30,970
(Laughing)

1147
00:45:31,070 --> 00:45:33,639
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you for the meal.

1148
00:45:33,640 --> 00:45:36,440
(After the eventful lunch)

1149
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:41,480
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

1150
00:45:42,310 --> 00:45:46,380
(Current time: 12:50pm)

1151
00:45:46,810 --> 00:45:49,720
(They've come home before the afternoon task.)

1152
00:45:51,390 --> 00:45:52,390
Gosh.

1153
00:45:52,391 --> 00:45:55,120
(Tired from working since early morning)

1154
00:45:55,690 --> 00:45:57,589
Do we leave at 1:40pm?

1155
00:45:57,590 --> 00:46:00,160
(They decided to take a short rest.)

1156
00:46:00,460 --> 00:46:01,460
Here.

1157
00:46:01,461 --> 00:46:02,500
(Protein drink)

1158
00:46:03,670 --> 00:46:04,769
Kyung Soo, do you want some protein?

1159
00:46:04,770 --> 00:46:05,900
(I'm good.)

1160
00:46:07,340 --> 00:46:09,499
- Have it before you sleep.
- We just had lunch.

1161
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:10,639
Drink it before you sleep.

1162
00:46:10,640 --> 00:46:11,640
I'm full.

1163
00:46:12,170 --> 00:46:13,979
Put up with it and overcome it!

1164
00:46:13,980 --> 00:46:15,410
I don't even work out.

1165
00:46:17,250 --> 00:46:20,250
(Planning to force Kyung Soo to drink it)

1166
00:46:21,650 --> 00:46:22,980
I'm not drinking it.

1167
00:46:23,690 --> 00:46:25,190
I'm not!

1168
00:46:25,720 --> 00:46:27,320
I'm not drinking it!

1169
00:46:27,760 --> 00:46:29,359
Drink it. It's good for your health.

1170
00:46:29,360 --> 00:46:31,229
I'm not, okay?

1171
00:46:31,230 --> 00:46:32,290
(Like a dad disciplining his picky-eater son)

1172
00:46:32,590 --> 00:46:34,099
No, don't open it.

1173
00:46:34,100 --> 00:46:35,199
It'll get on the covers.

1174
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:36,300
Don't open it.

1175
00:46:37,970 --> 00:46:39,969
- It'll get on your clothes.
- I'm full.

1176
00:46:39,970 --> 00:46:41,639
Drink it! It's good for your health!

1177
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:42,740
No, stop.

1178
00:46:43,840 --> 00:46:47,680
(In the end, Kyung Soo is being force-fed.)

1179
00:46:47,840 --> 00:46:48,910
Drink it yourself now.

1180
00:46:49,180 --> 00:46:52,950
(Only then does Kwang Soo drink his protein drink.)

1181
00:46:54,180 --> 00:46:58,050
(They lie down and take a short break.)

1182
00:46:59,220 --> 00:47:01,290
(A little while later)

1183
00:47:02,990 --> 00:47:04,360
Thank you.

1184
00:47:06,460 --> 00:47:07,929
They don't know I'm here, right?

1185
00:47:07,930 --> 00:47:08,930
No.

1186
00:47:08,931 --> 00:47:12,670
(The intern from the head office has arrived.)

1187
00:47:13,570 --> 00:47:14,639
(Intern Moon Sang Hoon)

1188
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:15,739
(Known for his roles such as...)

1189
00:47:15,740 --> 00:47:17,269
(Mr. Moon, Reporter Moon, and Hoonies)

1190
00:47:17,270 --> 00:47:18,369
We're just about to go in.

1191
00:47:18,370 --> 00:47:19,640
- Is this the house?
- Yes.

1192
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:22,209
This feels exactly like the moments before...

1193
00:47:22,210 --> 00:47:23,750
introducing myself after transferring schools.

1194
00:47:26,310 --> 00:47:28,080
The three are super close.

1195
00:47:28,350 --> 00:47:30,080
When you transfer schools,

1196
00:47:30,520 --> 00:47:32,450
the teacher tells everyone to get along with you.

1197
00:47:32,720 --> 00:47:34,390
But right now, I have to go in alone, right?

1198
00:47:34,620 --> 00:47:37,359
(The intern is extremely shy.)

1199
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:38,360
Do I just go in?

1200
00:47:39,630 --> 00:47:43,260
(Heading into the house, completely tensed up)

1201
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:50,740
(Opening)

1202
00:47:52,140 --> 00:47:53,140
(Closing)

1203
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:58,079
(Woo Bin walks away, not realizing the door has closed.)

1204
00:47:58,080 --> 00:47:59,080
Hi!

1205
00:47:59,081 --> 00:48:00,149
(Woo Bin walks away, not realizing the door has closed.)

1206
00:48:00,150 --> 00:48:01,150
Is anyone home?

1207
00:48:02,020 --> 00:48:04,850
I'm intern Moon Sang Hoon.

1208
00:48:06,590 --> 00:48:10,530
(Woo Bin senses someone's presence.)

1209
00:48:11,530 --> 00:48:12,530
What is it?

1210
00:48:14,860 --> 00:48:16,659
- What's going on?
- Hi, Woo Bin.

1211
00:48:16,660 --> 00:48:17,670
Who are you?

1212
00:48:18,670 --> 00:48:20,840
I came as an intern today.

1213
00:48:21,270 --> 00:48:22,739
Sang Hoon, I...

1214
00:48:22,740 --> 00:48:23,740
So you were washing up.

1215
00:48:23,741 --> 00:48:25,169
I'm in the middle of gargling.

1216
00:48:25,170 --> 00:48:27,279
- Come in.
- Gosh. Okay.

1217
00:48:27,280 --> 00:48:28,640
- Have you been well?
- Yes.

1218
00:48:29,110 --> 00:48:30,779
(The two have met before.)

1219
00:48:30,780 --> 00:48:31,780
- Pardon me.
- Go ahead.

1220
00:48:31,781 --> 00:48:33,919
- Sang Hoon?
- Hey, Kwang Soo.

1221
00:48:33,920 --> 00:48:35,780
(Sang Hoon has also met Kwang Soo before.)

1222
00:48:36,080 --> 00:48:37,189
- Hey.
- Were you taking a nap?

1223
00:48:37,190 --> 00:48:39,289
- Hey.
- Hi.

1224
00:48:39,290 --> 00:48:41,190
- You...
- What's going on?

1225
00:48:41,520 --> 00:48:42,520
Hi.

1226
00:48:43,090 --> 00:48:44,160
Hi.

1227
00:48:44,330 --> 00:48:46,729
I heard you had a rough morning.

1228
00:48:46,730 --> 00:48:48,560
I brought coffee.

1229
00:48:49,860 --> 00:48:50,870
Thanks.

1230
00:48:52,370 --> 00:48:54,069
(A strange situation with the arrival of the intern)

1231
00:48:54,070 --> 00:48:55,070
Here.

1232
00:48:55,570 --> 00:48:56,870
In the morning...

1233
00:48:59,340 --> 00:49:00,609
- Thanks, Sang Hoon.
- No problem.

1234
00:49:00,610 --> 00:49:02,609
- You've been well, yes?
- Yes.

1235
00:49:02,610 --> 00:49:03,810
Nice to meet you.

1236
00:49:04,680 --> 00:49:08,519
Were you taking a nap?

1237
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:09,819
- What...
- Were you in the middle of a nap?

1238
00:49:09,820 --> 00:49:10,820
I just woke up.

1239
00:49:13,190 --> 00:49:14,460
I'll go put on some pants.

1240
00:49:16,190 --> 00:49:19,160
(I'm going to spit this out.)

1241
00:49:20,290 --> 00:49:21,930
- Thanks for coming.
- Don't mention it.

1242
00:49:22,500 --> 00:49:24,200
By the way...

1243
00:49:25,530 --> 00:49:28,070
- What?
- I'm happy to be here.

1244
00:49:29,240 --> 00:49:30,270
(Laughing)

1245
00:49:31,540 --> 00:49:34,310
(It's awkward, like he's a new transfer student.)

1246
00:49:34,840 --> 00:49:36,709
- Do you know Kyung Soo?
- We've never met before.

1247
00:49:36,710 --> 00:49:38,710
- It's my first time meeting him.
- Is that so?

1248
00:49:40,050 --> 00:49:41,050
May I call you by your name?

1249
00:49:41,051 --> 00:49:42,250
Of course.

1250
00:49:42,820 --> 00:49:45,849
- Then I'll call you Mr. Kyung Soo.
- No.

1251
00:49:45,850 --> 00:49:46,850
Just call me by my name.

1252
00:49:47,220 --> 00:49:49,520
I'm bad at dropping honorifics, but I'll try.

1253
00:49:50,830 --> 00:49:52,389
I'll call you Sang Hoon.

1254
00:49:52,390 --> 00:49:53,390
Okay.

1255
00:49:53,590 --> 00:49:56,759
Sang Hoon, have you heard what we're doing?

1256
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:58,870
I only heard it was a farm.

1257
00:49:59,300 --> 00:50:01,199
Farms can have alpacas, horses, and things like that.

1258
00:50:01,200 --> 00:50:02,840
But my guess is cows.

1259
00:50:06,540 --> 00:50:07,540
Penguin?

1260
00:50:09,510 --> 00:50:11,549
Sang Hoon, are you acting right now?

1261
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:12,649
No.

1262
00:50:12,650 --> 00:50:15,579
- I don't know how to act right now.
- I can't read the room.

1263
00:50:15,580 --> 00:50:18,950
Is this all a skit or something?

1264
00:50:19,520 --> 00:50:22,759
Are you Moon Sang Hoon right now, or are you playing a character?

1265
00:50:22,760 --> 00:50:24,129
I'm Moon Sang Hoon right now.

1266
00:50:24,130 --> 00:50:25,489
Moon Sang Hoon?

1267
00:50:25,490 --> 00:50:27,190
Yes. But you see...

1268
00:50:28,360 --> 00:50:30,430
I'm currently Moon Sang Hoon.

1269
00:50:33,070 --> 00:50:34,570
- Moon Sang Hoon.
- You're not being yourself.

1270
00:50:34,640 --> 00:50:35,640
You're not like yourself.

1271
00:50:35,641 --> 00:50:37,470
The thing is...

1272
00:50:38,010 --> 00:50:40,539
Everyone here is already close to each other.

1273
00:50:40,540 --> 00:50:42,209
But I only joined today.

1274
00:50:42,210 --> 00:50:44,279
It's not easy to get along with everyone as if...

1275
00:50:44,280 --> 00:50:45,750
I've been here from the beginning.

1276
00:50:48,720 --> 00:50:51,089
Don't force me to make myself at home.

1277
00:50:51,090 --> 00:50:52,850
That only makes me more uncomfortable.

1278
00:50:53,390 --> 00:50:55,260
I'll find my own pace.

1279
00:50:55,390 --> 00:50:56,390
(An intern who speaks his mind)

1280
00:50:56,391 --> 00:50:58,329
I'm not nagging you.

1281
00:50:58,330 --> 00:51:00,760
You seem different from a few minutes ago.

1282
00:51:02,300 --> 00:51:03,300
This is the real him.

1283
00:51:03,301 --> 00:51:04,669
- Really?
- Anyway, I'll find...

1284
00:51:04,670 --> 00:51:06,229
You've been on many shows before.

1285
00:51:06,230 --> 00:51:07,299
True.

1286
00:51:07,300 --> 00:51:09,940
But this is who I genuinely am.

1287
00:51:11,310 --> 00:51:13,139
I personally think it'd look much more fake...

1288
00:51:13,140 --> 00:51:15,110
if I acted overly familiar.

1289
00:51:15,640 --> 00:51:17,450
I can definitely make myself at home.

1290
00:51:17,910 --> 00:51:19,049
I totally can.

1291
00:51:19,050 --> 00:51:21,149
But that'd be me forcing myself to do it.

1292
00:51:21,150 --> 00:51:22,680
I'm fine as I am right now.

1293
00:51:25,250 --> 00:51:27,820
(The intern is far from ordinary.)

1294
00:51:28,960 --> 00:51:30,459
(Do you really feel comfortable?)

1295
00:51:30,460 --> 00:51:31,690
Does it look fake?

1296
00:51:34,700 --> 00:51:37,330
Honestly, it's just awkward.

1297
00:51:37,930 --> 00:51:39,070
It can only be awkward, you know?

1298
00:51:39,670 --> 00:51:41,840
(That's normal on the first day at a new school.)

1299
00:51:44,840 --> 00:51:48,040
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

1300
00:51:49,140 --> 00:51:50,309
You have to meet the CEO of this farm first.

1301
00:51:50,310 --> 00:51:52,480
- You haven't met the CEO, have you?
- No.

1302
00:51:53,610 --> 00:51:55,480
Sir, our intern is here.

1303
00:51:55,780 --> 00:51:58,490
- He's the CEO.
- Hello, sir.

1304
00:51:59,450 --> 00:52:00,450
Nice to meet you.

1305
00:52:00,451 --> 00:52:01,960
Hi. My name is Moon Sang Hoon.

1306
00:52:03,560 --> 00:52:04,929
Right, nice to meet you.

1307
00:52:04,930 --> 00:52:06,759
- Nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

1308
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:08,830
- He's our intern.
- I see.

1309
00:52:09,130 --> 00:52:11,199
Learn the ropes, okay?

1310
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:12,270
Of course.

1311
00:52:12,830 --> 00:52:14,540
- Kkalloo!
- Yes?

1312
00:52:14,770 --> 00:52:16,269
Kkalloo, our intern is here.

1313
00:52:16,270 --> 00:52:18,810
- Hi. My name is Moon Sang Hoon.
- He's Kkalloo.

1314
00:52:19,310 --> 00:52:21,480
We have Lal too, who must be taking a nap somewhere.

1315
00:52:23,810 --> 00:52:24,880
- Sang Hoon.
- Yes?

1316
00:52:25,050 --> 00:52:27,080
Would you like to put this on?

1317
00:52:28,620 --> 00:52:31,489
(Trying on the boots with the straw hat from Kwang Soo)

1318
00:52:31,490 --> 00:52:34,260
(Wrinkly)

1319
00:52:36,290 --> 00:52:37,690
- Do the boots fit?
- Yes.

1320
00:52:37,760 --> 00:52:39,630
But are they supposed to be this wrinkly?

1321
00:52:41,260 --> 00:52:43,860
(Wrinkly)

1322
00:52:46,500 --> 00:52:48,040
They must be the baby cows.

1323
00:52:49,770 --> 00:52:51,240
- Juvenile cows.
- Juvenile cows.

1324
00:52:53,540 --> 00:52:55,439
(A camera he brought himself)

1325
00:52:55,440 --> 00:52:57,040
(Laughing)

1326
00:52:58,810 --> 00:53:01,750
(Sang Hoon spent some time healing with the cows.)

1327
00:53:02,920 --> 00:53:03,920
(It's time to start working.)

1328
00:53:03,920 --> 00:53:04,920
Let's go.

1329
00:53:08,960 --> 00:53:11,460
These are garlic peels from Nonghyup.

1330
00:53:11,960 --> 00:53:14,129
They're a byproduct from processing garlic.

1331
00:53:14,130 --> 00:53:16,129
We'll spread these out for the cows.

1332
00:53:16,130 --> 00:53:17,969
- I see.
- And so...

1333
00:53:17,970 --> 00:53:19,029
(The garlic peels will be spread out on the barn floor.)

1334
00:53:19,030 --> 00:53:21,040
We've got 17 sacks right now.

1335
00:53:21,370 --> 00:53:23,969
- The garlic peels make it comfy...
- Yes.

1336
00:53:23,970 --> 00:53:25,709
- and less humid.
- Right.

1337
00:53:25,710 --> 00:53:27,039
They also work as a natural disinfectant.

1338
00:53:27,040 --> 00:53:29,009
- Disinfectant?
- That's right.

1339
00:53:29,010 --> 00:53:30,610
- It helps with the humidity.
- Nice.

1340
00:53:31,510 --> 00:53:32,679
How do we do it?

1341
00:53:32,680 --> 00:53:34,619
Let's head over there.

1342
00:53:34,620 --> 00:53:35,849
- Tractor?
- With a tractor.

1343
00:53:35,850 --> 00:53:36,880
- Got it.
- We have to transfer it.

1344
00:53:38,650 --> 00:53:39,690
What's that?

1345
00:53:40,820 --> 00:53:42,690
- Are those all garlic peels?
- Yes, for the floor.

1346
00:53:42,860 --> 00:53:44,329
That's a lot.

1347
00:53:44,330 --> 00:53:45,330
(Big sacks of garlic peels await them.)

1348
00:53:45,830 --> 00:53:46,889
Those are a bit too much.

1349
00:53:46,890 --> 00:53:48,759
Do we spread them on the floor?

1350
00:53:48,760 --> 00:53:49,900
(These garlic peel sacks)

1351
00:53:51,070 --> 00:53:53,730
(Where around 80 cows are)

1352
00:53:54,340 --> 00:53:56,940
(The 3,967m² milking parlor)

1353
00:53:57,810 --> 00:54:00,810
(Must be spread across the entire floor)

1354
00:54:01,840 --> 00:54:04,950
(The training has become more intense with the extra help.)

1355
00:54:05,680 --> 00:54:08,220
(Current time: 2pm, Spread out garlic peels)

1356
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:11,920
The liquid is pee...

1357
00:54:11,990 --> 00:54:13,689
and the rest is poop, right?

1358
00:54:13,690 --> 00:54:15,119
(A sudden question from the beginner)

1359
00:54:15,120 --> 00:54:16,489
- Don't think about it too much.
- Okay.

1360
00:54:16,490 --> 00:54:17,660
Ignore the details.

1361
00:54:18,830 --> 00:54:19,860
If...

1362
00:54:20,560 --> 00:54:22,329
you imagine it's dirt, it feels like just dirt.

1363
00:54:22,330 --> 00:54:24,029
- Like mud, right?
- Yes.

1364
00:54:24,030 --> 00:54:25,700
There are times when you can...

1365
00:54:25,770 --> 00:54:27,170
- really smell it.
- I see.

1366
00:54:27,770 --> 00:54:29,939
- If you try not to breathe...
- Got it.

1367
00:54:29,940 --> 00:54:31,510
- Breathe with your mouth.
- Okay.

1368
00:54:34,580 --> 00:54:36,139
- Yes?
- If you hook the sack...

1369
00:54:36,140 --> 00:54:37,279
and pull it up,

1370
00:54:37,280 --> 00:54:38,809
- the garlic peels spill out.
- Okay.

1371
00:54:38,810 --> 00:54:40,919
You just have to...

1372
00:54:40,920 --> 00:54:42,820
- spread them out.
- All right.

1373
00:54:43,850 --> 00:54:46,490
(Pour the garlic peels out by hooking the sack onto the tractor.)

1374
00:54:46,950 --> 00:54:49,259
(Spread the garlic peels out on the barn floor.)

1375
00:54:49,260 --> 00:54:50,490
So you just spread them out.

1376
00:54:51,090 --> 00:54:54,430
(The skill training has begun.)

1377
00:54:58,770 --> 00:55:00,570
- This feels nice.
- I know, right?

1378
00:55:02,600 --> 00:55:03,969
Don't they look like cherry blossoms?

1379
00:55:03,970 --> 00:55:05,210
- They do.
- Right?

1380
00:55:05,410 --> 00:55:07,010
- They don't smell half bad.
- No.

1381
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:09,410
It's kind of tasty.

1382
00:55:10,780 --> 00:55:11,850
Right.

1383
00:55:15,580 --> 00:55:16,650
What are you eating?

1384
00:55:17,850 --> 00:55:18,920
What are you eating?

1385
00:55:19,090 --> 00:55:21,120
Garlic. They must be looking for garlic.

1386
00:55:21,190 --> 00:55:22,260
It seems like it.

1387
00:55:24,020 --> 00:55:27,660
(An animal-bonding type)

1388
00:55:29,760 --> 00:55:33,069
(Focused only on garlic)

1389
00:55:33,070 --> 00:55:36,170
(An efficiency-first type)

1390
00:55:37,340 --> 00:55:40,310
(Using his forearm muscles to full use)

1391
00:55:41,240 --> 00:55:44,110
(An upper-body workout type)

1392
00:55:45,480 --> 00:55:47,949
(Slow)

1393
00:55:47,950 --> 00:55:49,979
Nobody has tripped, have they?

1394
00:55:49,980 --> 00:55:51,750
- Nobody has tripped, right?
- Not yet.

1395
00:55:53,290 --> 00:55:56,620
(A terrified-of-poop type)

1396
00:55:57,060 --> 00:55:59,259
It feels much better than yesterday.

1397
00:55:59,260 --> 00:56:01,729
Yesterday's were heavy, but these are light.

1398
00:56:01,730 --> 00:56:02,730
Right.

1399
00:56:02,760 --> 00:56:04,900
These remind me of flowers.

1400
00:56:05,230 --> 00:56:06,230
- What?
- Flowers.

1401
00:56:06,231 --> 00:56:08,240
- They do look like flowers.
- Right?

1402
00:56:09,840 --> 00:56:11,939
(Shouting)

1403
00:56:11,940 --> 00:56:13,169
(Moving to the next area...)

1404
00:56:13,170 --> 00:56:14,910
(after driving the cows to the finished part)

1405
00:56:15,110 --> 00:56:16,180
They're rubbing against it.

1406
00:56:16,380 --> 00:56:18,250
(Rubbing)

1407
00:56:22,280 --> 00:56:25,090
(Pouring the garlic peels out)

1408
00:56:29,820 --> 00:56:34,600
(Spreading out the garlic peels once again)

1409
00:56:36,330 --> 00:56:39,470
(There's still a ton left to spread.)

1410
00:56:40,400 --> 00:56:43,170
(Many sacks still need to be emptied.)

1411
00:56:43,770 --> 00:56:46,040
(In need of the perfect work song)

1412
00:56:52,080 --> 00:56:56,250
(As if spring has come to the barn,)

1413
00:56:57,520 --> 00:57:00,420
(garlic petals flutter through the air.)

1414
00:57:04,290 --> 00:57:06,360
Yesterday, I felt like I'd become poop.

1415
00:57:08,730 --> 00:57:10,860
Today, I feel like I've become garlic.

1416
00:57:12,300 --> 00:57:14,070
But it smelled quite nice.

1417
00:57:16,570 --> 00:57:17,970
The smell of garlic was great.

1418
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:22,010
The smell of garlic was amazing.

1419
00:57:24,140 --> 00:57:28,020
(The trainees are getting drunk on the scent of garlic.)

1420
00:57:29,020 --> 00:57:32,920
(An endless cycle of garlic peel sacks)

1421
00:57:33,990 --> 00:57:37,590
(An hour has passed of spreading endless garlic peel sacks.)

1422
00:57:38,490 --> 00:57:39,860
This isn't easy either.

1423
00:57:40,930 --> 00:57:42,759
- Sorry?
- This isn't easy, is it?

1424
00:57:42,760 --> 00:57:45,470
(The trainees are tired.)

1425
00:57:46,600 --> 00:57:49,700
(At that moment, Kyung Soo walks off somewhere.)

1426
00:57:51,110 --> 00:57:54,210
(Trainee Kyung Soo is headed toward...)

1427
00:57:57,950 --> 00:58:00,409
(the air blower they used in the morning?)

1428
00:58:00,410 --> 00:58:01,780
Are you going to use it?

1429
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:03,350
We've got this, right?

1430
00:58:04,390 --> 00:58:06,220
We've got an incredible tool.

1431
00:58:09,990 --> 00:58:12,930
(He comes in with the air blower.)

1432
00:58:13,630 --> 00:58:14,730
Kwang Soo.

1433
00:58:15,430 --> 00:58:16,599
Did you bring that in?

1434
00:58:16,600 --> 00:58:18,000
Do you mind stepping aside?

1435
00:58:19,130 --> 00:58:20,330
- Let me try.
- Okay.

1436
00:58:25,891 --> 00:58:29,391
(Efficient to the max)

1437
00:58:29,731 --> 00:58:31,630
(How did you come up with using the air blower?)

1438
00:58:31,631 --> 00:58:33,001
It just popped into my head.

1439
00:58:34,061 --> 00:58:36,101
The garlic peels are light. If I blew them around,

1440
00:58:36,571 --> 00:58:37,741
wouldn't it be easy?

1441
00:58:39,371 --> 00:58:40,441
Efficiency.

1442
00:58:41,371 --> 00:58:42,471
Practicality.

1443
00:58:43,541 --> 00:58:44,641
It's unbelievable.

1444
00:58:45,211 --> 00:58:47,011
(Smiling brightly)

1445
00:58:49,051 --> 00:58:52,350
(What do you think about Kyung Soo's air blower idea?)

1446
00:58:52,351 --> 00:58:54,551
Using Bongbong...

1447
00:58:55,291 --> 00:58:57,120
With that...

1448
00:58:57,121 --> 00:58:59,290
That never crossed our minds until now.

1449
00:58:59,291 --> 00:59:00,561
He's brilliant.

1450
00:59:01,761 --> 00:59:02,831
Good idea.

1451
00:59:03,661 --> 00:59:05,461
I should give him a thumbs up.

1452
00:59:07,871 --> 00:59:11,001
(He received the CEO's thumbs up.)

1453
00:59:11,571 --> 00:59:14,000
- That's amazing, Kyung Soo.
- Right?

1454
00:59:14,001 --> 00:59:15,810
- You thought of it, right?
- Yes.

1455
00:59:15,811 --> 00:59:16,841
I knew it.

1456
00:59:17,671 --> 00:59:20,881
(With Kyung Soo's air blower magic,)

1457
00:59:21,511 --> 00:59:25,921
(only the last area is left in no time.)

1458
00:59:26,951 --> 00:59:29,690
(The intern works on the garlic peel sack.)

1459
00:59:29,691 --> 00:59:30,951
Don't untie it.

1460
00:59:31,121 --> 00:59:32,421
- Don't untie it.
- Got it.

1461
00:59:34,391 --> 00:59:35,431
- Sang Hoon.
- Yes?

1462
00:59:36,661 --> 00:59:39,830
- You weren't told to do it, right?
- No.

1463
00:59:39,831 --> 00:59:40,861
Don't...

1464
00:59:41,001 --> 00:59:42,001
Got it.

1465
00:59:42,001 --> 00:59:43,001
(Discouraged)

1466
00:59:43,831 --> 00:59:45,900
(Trying to put the sack away)

1467
00:59:45,901 --> 00:59:47,941
(Failed as the auditor did it first)

1468
00:59:49,171 --> 00:59:50,341
Sang Hoon, the rope.

1469
00:59:51,511 --> 00:59:54,710
(Failed to put the sack away and took the rope they still needed)

1470
00:59:54,711 --> 00:59:57,150
(How was your first training?)

1471
00:59:57,151 --> 00:59:58,851
When I heard it was a farm,

1472
00:59:59,521 --> 01:00:01,590
I thought we'd herd sheep or do something...

1473
01:00:01,591 --> 01:00:02,691
on a peaceful farm.

1474
01:00:03,291 --> 01:00:04,390
(Inhaling)

1475
01:00:04,391 --> 01:00:05,720
The daily grind.

1476
01:00:05,721 --> 01:00:06,991
It was quite...

1477
01:00:07,931 --> 01:00:09,531
Well, it was quite...

1478
01:00:11,931 --> 01:00:13,061
I haven't had such a tiring day in a while.

1479
01:00:14,931 --> 01:00:17,501
(Not helpful, though he wants to be)

1480
01:00:17,801 --> 01:00:18,871
All good.

1481
01:00:20,871 --> 01:00:21,971
All good.

1482
01:00:22,271 --> 01:00:25,341
(The intern copies anything that looks cool.)

1483
01:00:26,441 --> 01:00:27,441
(Glancing)

1484
01:00:28,911 --> 01:00:32,281
(The director's air blower is a culture shock.)

1485
01:00:33,081 --> 01:00:34,321
(Air blower off)

1486
01:00:35,151 --> 01:00:37,791
(The director left his air blower behind.)

1487
01:00:39,121 --> 01:00:41,861
(Quickening footsteps)

1488
01:00:43,391 --> 01:00:45,801
(He acquired the director's air blower.)

1489
01:00:48,831 --> 01:00:50,201
(Spotting)

1490
01:00:51,141 --> 01:00:53,371
If he's holding it, it means that he's struggling.

1491
01:00:54,611 --> 01:00:56,671
As the work is hard...

1492
01:00:56,771 --> 01:01:00,110
(How was the director's air blower?)

1493
01:01:00,111 --> 01:01:01,551
I tried it.

1494
01:01:02,211 --> 01:01:04,051
It was definitely faster.

1495
01:01:05,221 --> 01:01:09,020
(The owner of the air blower is right behind you.)

1496
01:01:09,021 --> 01:01:11,490
(Silent)

1497
01:01:11,491 --> 01:01:13,521
All right, it's tired.

1498
01:01:14,191 --> 01:01:15,261
It's tired.

1499
01:01:15,361 --> 01:01:16,391
- Sang Hoon.
- Yes?

1500
01:01:17,061 --> 01:01:19,031
When I was an intern, I didn't even dream of using that machine.

1501
01:01:20,801 --> 01:01:21,901
I couldn't even go near it.

1502
01:01:24,801 --> 01:01:26,541
When I was an intern, I did it by hand.

1503
01:01:28,011 --> 01:01:30,141
(Sighing)

1504
01:01:31,311 --> 01:01:34,281
(The intern swallows his nerves after using the air blower once.)

1505
01:01:35,251 --> 01:01:37,111
I think we're done spreading it out.

1506
01:01:38,351 --> 01:01:40,351
Having one more person really makes it faster.

1507
01:01:40,451 --> 01:01:42,120
It feels much quicker now.

1508
01:01:42,121 --> 01:01:43,121
- Really?
- Right?

1509
01:01:43,451 --> 01:01:45,560
- We finished quickly.
- I know.

1510
01:01:45,561 --> 01:01:48,260
(A barn where cherry blossoms seem to fall...)

1511
01:01:48,261 --> 01:01:50,960
(within 2 hours of afternoon training)

1512
01:01:50,961 --> 01:01:51,961
We're done.

1513
01:01:54,461 --> 01:01:56,671
What are you doing? You must be excited.

1514
01:01:57,401 --> 01:01:58,770
They must be very pleased.

1515
01:01:58,771 --> 01:02:00,271
This one seems full of curiosity.

1516
01:02:00,741 --> 01:02:01,811
Do you want to play?

1517
01:02:04,111 --> 01:02:06,981
(They became close enough to joke around with the cows.)

1518
01:02:07,081 --> 01:02:08,980
Sir. We're done here, right?

1519
01:02:08,981 --> 01:02:10,381
There's some more left.

1520
01:02:11,081 --> 01:02:13,181
Since we're at it, let's do the other side too.

1521
01:02:13,881 --> 01:02:15,351
"Since we're at it?"

1522
01:02:15,951 --> 01:02:18,091
Shouldn't you show something?

1523
01:02:18,621 --> 01:02:20,421
We showed everything we've got.

1524
01:02:20,991 --> 01:02:22,791
We even have an intern now.

1525
01:02:24,901 --> 01:02:27,330
You worked so hard. Do the other side as well.

1526
01:02:27,331 --> 01:02:28,701
I'm feeling ambitious.

1527
01:02:29,601 --> 01:02:31,301
Since when were you so greedy?

1528
01:02:32,141 --> 01:02:33,270
Don't be greedy.

1529
01:02:33,271 --> 01:02:34,271
(On the brink of a disaster)

1530
01:02:35,541 --> 01:02:37,011
Do we get any snack break?

1531
01:02:42,111 --> 01:02:45,621
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

1532
01:02:46,051 --> 01:02:48,051
CEO Lee, let's make a plan before we continue.

1533
01:02:48,421 --> 01:02:49,421
What plan?

1534
01:02:49,991 --> 01:02:52,261
This place must be...

1535
01:02:53,261 --> 01:02:54,261
the meeting space.

1536
01:02:54,262 --> 01:02:55,961
Yes, let's have a meeting here.

1537
01:02:56,331 --> 01:02:57,361
Senior Lal.

1538
01:02:58,331 --> 01:02:59,461
Hey, Kkalloo.

1539
01:03:00,031 --> 01:03:04,840
Give them your wage for today...

1540
01:03:04,841 --> 01:03:06,101
since you didn't do any work.

1541
01:03:07,441 --> 01:03:09,611
- Where were you?
- Senior Kkalloo has changed.

1542
01:03:09,911 --> 01:03:11,941
No, I was there too.

1543
01:03:14,041 --> 01:03:16,081
- Mr. Kkalloo, please sit.
- Have a seat.

1544
01:03:16,551 --> 01:03:19,081
Are you willing to give your wages to them?

1545
01:03:20,021 --> 01:03:22,491
Do you intend to pay them?

1546
01:03:22,691 --> 01:03:23,721
No.

1547
01:03:24,191 --> 01:03:26,521
(Speaking in Korean firmly)

1548
01:03:26,821 --> 01:03:28,731
Since when were you this fluent in Korean?

1549
01:03:29,891 --> 01:03:30,891
We're just joking.

1550
01:03:31,601 --> 01:03:33,160
(Suddenly getting up)

1551
01:03:33,161 --> 01:03:36,871
I should've returned it.

1552
01:03:37,001 --> 01:03:38,971
- What?
- That machine.

1553
01:03:39,071 --> 01:03:40,841
No, it's okay. Thank you.

1554
01:03:41,941 --> 01:03:43,511
- So you came all the way here?
- Yes.

1555
01:03:45,081 --> 01:03:49,211
Do you really think that version of you suits you?

1556
01:03:49,581 --> 01:03:50,581
(Giggling)

1557
01:03:50,582 --> 01:03:51,881
(The director finally broke away from being the youngest.)

1558
01:03:52,051 --> 01:03:53,681
It's coming out.

1559
01:03:54,721 --> 01:03:56,451
(At that moment, a cow dreams of escape.)

1560
01:03:56,791 --> 01:03:57,791
Can it come out?

1561
01:03:57,792 --> 01:03:59,260
No.

1562
01:03:59,261 --> 01:04:01,221
It can't?

1563
01:04:01,591 --> 01:04:02,630
(The yodeling man bolts after it.)

1564
01:04:02,631 --> 01:04:03,991
(Chanting)

1565
01:04:04,291 --> 01:04:05,901
(Shouting)

1566
01:04:06,001 --> 01:04:08,171
(Now he can handle cattle driving on his own.)

1567
01:04:09,701 --> 01:04:10,971
For the remaining work,

1568
01:04:11,971 --> 01:04:14,671
if we team up with others, we'll finish it quickly.

1569
01:04:14,971 --> 01:04:16,811
We'll do it,

1570
01:04:17,511 --> 01:04:20,581
but by playing foot volleyball...

1571
01:04:21,181 --> 01:04:24,311
- By playing a game?
- Let's play a simple game.

1572
01:04:25,021 --> 01:04:26,521
- If we win, - Yes?

1573
01:04:27,621 --> 01:04:29,151
everyone will come together...

1574
01:04:29,251 --> 01:04:30,721
and finish the work all at once.

1575
01:04:31,321 --> 01:04:34,060
If we lose,

1576
01:04:34,061 --> 01:04:36,331
the four of us will finish up the work.

1577
01:04:36,891 --> 01:04:37,930
What do you think?

1578
01:04:37,931 --> 01:04:39,200
Can you run the tractor?

1579
01:04:39,201 --> 01:04:40,231
- What?
- The tractor.

1580
01:04:40,601 --> 01:04:41,800
- A moment ago...
- I can't do it.

1581
01:04:41,801 --> 01:04:43,330
Please run the tractor for us.

1582
01:04:43,331 --> 01:04:45,471
That means I'll do all the work.

1583
01:04:45,841 --> 01:04:47,901
We can also run the tractor.

1584
01:04:48,271 --> 01:04:49,311
(Getting up)

1585
01:04:49,411 --> 01:04:50,611
Hey.

1586
01:04:51,381 --> 01:04:54,851
Hey!

1587
01:04:55,411 --> 01:04:56,450
(Chanting)

1588
01:04:56,451 --> 01:04:58,120
(Imitating Kwang Soo's yodeling cattle drive)

1589
01:04:58,121 --> 01:04:59,220
Hey.

1590
01:04:59,221 --> 01:05:01,351
(Chanting)

1591
01:05:03,021 --> 01:05:04,551
He looks like the wasp guy.

1592
01:05:06,961 --> 01:05:09,391
The one who runs off in the middle of a conversation?

1593
01:05:10,161 --> 01:05:13,060
How about us making lunch for you tomorrow?

1594
01:05:13,061 --> 01:05:14,600
- If we lose.
- We make a meal?

1595
01:05:14,601 --> 01:05:16,500
Yes, if we lose.

1596
01:05:16,501 --> 01:05:18,441
- Making breakfast?
- Who's going to cook?

1597
01:05:19,341 --> 01:05:20,441
We'll cook together.

1598
01:05:20,641 --> 01:05:22,471
We'll cook together with you as the chef.

1599
